ad parents, two cypresses, several young nurses crouching around, and a family doctor so old as to be almost invisible. Perhaps because of my stumblings and fits of coughing the story of my poor Laura had less success with my listeners than it will have, I hope, with intelligent reviewers when properly published.





Vladimir Nabokov





TO: PROF. SIMON KARLINSKY

TL (XEROX), 1 p.





Montreux-Palace Hotel

1820 Montreux, Switzerland

January 3, 1977

